DemoFlowchart <pre><code>flowchart TD
  A[PlanSwift ▸ New Job] --&gt; B[Name Your Job];
  B --&gt; C[Set Your Margins];
  C --&gt; D[Select Your Floor Plan Image Files];
  D --&gt;E[Finish];</code></pre>

DemoFlowchart <pre><code>flowchart TD
  A[Create Takeoff Item] --&gt; B[Name Takeoff Item];
  B -- Optional --&gt; C[Create &amp; Name The Folder];
  C --&gt; D;
  B --&gt; D[Count/Measure With Takeoff Item];
  D --&gt; E[Drag &amp; Drop Prebuilt Millwork Template Assembly Items Onto Takeoff];
  E --&gt; F[Set Qty Per Count Property];
  F --&gt; G[View In Estimating Tab];
  G --&gt; H[Use Custom Layouts To Display Data];</code></pre>

DemoFlowchart <pre><code>flowchart TD
  A[Adjust Margins] -- Use Plugin --&gt; B[Select Margin To Adjust];
  A -- Use Job Property Form --&gt; C[PlanSwift Logo ▸ Job Properties];

  C --&gt; I[Set Margin Percentage Values];
  I --&gt; J[Click OK];
  J --&gt; F;

  B --&gt; D[Set Percentage Value];
  D --&gt; E[Click Refresh To Update Pricing];
  E --&gt; F[Use Custom Reports To Generate A Quote];</code></pre> <p>Very Important</p> <p></p> This is the proper way to structure PlanSwift Parent/Child Items so that data is properly displayed on PlanSwift Reports. For more details about individual items please see ▸ Field Definitions PlanSwift ScreenshotText Tree <p></p> <p>Folder └─ Segment (For measuring linear feet)  |     └─ Assembly (Container of items) Ex. door, trim, closet, etc.  |           ├─ Material (Inventory items with SKU &amp; Cost data)  |           ├─ Part (Same as Material items)  |           ├─ Labor (Inhouse manufacturing labor)  |           ├─ Subcontract (Install labor)  |           └─ Other (Option items) └─ Count (For counting qty)      └─ Assembly (Container of items) Ex. door, trim, closet, etc.            ├─ Material (Inventory items with SKU &amp; Cost data)            ├─ Part (Same as Material items)            ├─ Labor (Inhouse manufacturing labor)            ├─ Subcontract (Install labor)            └─ Other (Option items)  </p>

DemoFlowchart <pre><code>flowchart TD
  A[Navigate To Lists Tab] --&gt; B[Find Millwork Databases List Item];
  B --&gt; C[Access External Items Costs Table];
  C --&gt; D[Use Green + Button To Create A New Entry];
  D --&gt; E[Enter SKU #, Description &amp; Date Data For Your New Entry];
  E --&gt; F[Click Check Mark To Save Your Changes];
  F --&gt; G["Create Your #quot;Other#quot; Type Option Item"];</code></pre>

DemoFlowchart <pre><code>flowchart TD
  A[Create Your Desired Assembly Structure] -- IF NEEDED --&gt; B[Credit Material Via The Material Form];
  A --&gt; C;
  B --&gt; C[Add The External #quot;Other#quot; Type Item To The Assembly];
  C --&gt; D[Verify Qty Per Count &amp; Cost/Pricing Values Are Correct In Estimating Tab];</code></pre>

DemoFlowchart <pre><code>flowchart TD
  A[Navigate To The Reports Tab] --&gt; B[Select The Millwork Option/Credit By Folder Report];
  B --&gt; C[Review Data Displayed On The Report];</code></pre>
